<Content>Honeymoon RODENTS! All we wanted was a one-night stay near the airport, in order to catch an early morning flight. Well, there was to be NO sleep and NO rest to be found. The hotel had RATS! After trying more than one room, only to find MORE RATS, and with the manager not being available at that time , we felt we had to get out of there,and attempt to get some sleep at the airport: SIX HOURS early! We had stayed at all kinds of hotels in Mexico: from cheap to expensive, but we had NEVER experienced this before. The hotel had surely had complaints before, and nature says that if there is ONE rodent then there are MORE to be found. So why had nothing been done??What an awful ending to our honeymoon trip.This hotel should be closed until it gets Health Inspectors' approval.Shame on Holiday Inn! 
