<Author>Littlelobo
<Content>OK place to stay for one night Stayed here for one night, June 14, 2007 and selected this hotel because of the free shuttle to the Airport. This was convenient for me as I had a 7 a.m. departure flight. This hotel is only 5-10 minutes away but there are other hotels closer than this one. Upon entering the hotel, I was immediately assaulted by the smell of cigarette smoking. It was almost like walking into a casino in Las Vegas, extremely unpleasant!! The hotel itself is very nice inside but I was not impressed by the people at the reception desk. No welcome greeting, no asking how I was doing, nothing, just very robotic in their performance. The room I had was very large, but the bed was like sleeping on the floor. It was extremely hard. I also didn't feel safe as my room was located right next to the EXIT door and being by mself, I did not feel comfortable there. I was glad to be there for only one night. I don't plan to stay there again. 
