<Author>hashilla
<Content>Wonderful surprise By chance, we had a last minute delay to Ixtapa from LA and had to stay overnight in Mexico City. I called Holiday Inn randomly from the airport in LA to find a room. The operator suggested Plaza Dali. As it was so last minute and our first time in M.C., we were apprehensive about where to stay. I don't know about the other hotels, but our experience at the Dali was great.Wewere very surprised to be picked up via shuttle at the airport (quick 15 minute ride to the hotel) and the staff was so friendly. The gave us great suggestions as to where to go for dinner and nightlife. They had a private drive on standby who drove us to the La Condesa area for our evening out and picked us up when we were ready to come back.The rooms were simple but comfortable and they had an acceptable gym on our floor. Breakfast in the morning was nice, the juice was fresh and the service was extraordinary.Overall, we had a nice stay and I would recommend it to any traveler. 
